cs.DS, cs.RO, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper presents two methods to compress the description of a route in a road network, which involves graph algorithms and data structures.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper proposes the application of the methods to mobile server-based routing, which can be relevant to autonomous vehicles and robotics.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper discusses the transmission of computed routes using mobile radio communication, which involves networking and communication protocols.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper mentions the compression of route descriptions to save costs and transmission time, which can be related to information theory and data compression.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a less likely category, but the proposed application of the methods to mobile server-based routing can be relevant to control systems and optimization.
